procedures.name: Venipuncture
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), clinical laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation), pregnancy testing, and viral screening.

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy testing, and measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Fecal Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A complete physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vitals
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and other clinically significant findings.

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.name: Medical History Collection
procedures.label: Medical History
procedures.description: Collection of participant's medical history, Wilson disease history, and demographics.

procedures.name: Height, Weight, and BMI Measurement
procedures.label: Anthropometric Measurements
procedures.description: Measurement of participant's height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.label: UDS
procedures.description: Screening of urine for presence of drugs.

procedures.name: HIV, Hepatitis B and C Screening
procedures.label: Viral Screening
procedures.description: Blood test to screen for Human Immunodeficiency Virus, Hepatitis B, and Hepatitis C.

procedures.name: Serum/Urine Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Testing of serum or urine to detect pregnancy in females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Ongoing monitoring and collection of information on adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Neurological Assessment
procedures.label: Neuro Assessment
procedures.description: Monitoring for neurologic adverse events and neurological dysfunction. The Unified Wilson Disease Rating Scale (UWDRS) is mentioned as a relevant measure.

procedures.name: 24-hour Urine Collection
procedures.label: 24h Urine Collection
procedures.description: Collection of all urine produced over a 24-hour period for measurement of copper and molybdenum.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

medicalDevices.name: Intravenous Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure and Heart Rate Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Automated Vitals Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device to assess blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Analytical instrument used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
